# Railway: root = this repo, build `npm run build`, start `node scripts/start-standalone.cjs` (or `npm start`).
# Railway sets PORT (often 8080). The app listens on PORT — your public domain "target port" MUST match PORT,
# not 3000. If healthcheck passes but the browser gets 502, fix Networking → public URL port vs PORT.
# Copy variables above into Railway; set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your production URL.
